  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Public Financial Management, Anti-Corruption and Accountability Institutions &#x2013; BAN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Monitor the government&apos;s compliance with revenue generation provisions and commitments in the budget speech and Finance Act of 2019 
- Track government domestic revenue collection at national and local council levels and disseminate the information
- Conduct a tax payers perception survey on tax collection, processes and its use
- Develop policy briefs on transparency in granting duty waivers 
- Hold expert discussions on duty waivers and implications for revenue generation
- Track budget credibility (disbursement against commitments) from MoF to Ministries of Health and Education (quarterly) and the deliverables (six monthly)
- Facilitate pre-budget meeting of rights-based organizations for disability, gender and other diversities with MDAs to present needs for consideration into budgeting process
- Carry out Deep Dive&#xA0;studies looking at Education (teaching and learning materials) and Health (Free Health Care Drugs &#x2013; procurement, storage, distribution and utilization)
- Develop and produce scorecards on the report of the Auditor General</narrative>
  </description>
